XLIII. ¹ Provincias inter se paraverant] I think that Gronov. in his Observat. lib. 1, c. 10, pp. 91, 92, has proved from lib. 8, and lib. 25, of Livy, that paraverant is as good a reading here as partiverant. It means, they had settled, or arranged. He shows that evenire does not always convey the idea of lot, but sometimes of a simple arrangement.
